The paper deals with the problem of securely computing a function over a wiretap channel, which involves information theory and cryptography. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves computation and algorithms, which suggests cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as possible sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with distributed sources and multiple-access channels, which suggests cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as another possible sub-category.
